CAPE TOWN – The National Union of Mineworkers (NUM) has declared a dispute with Sibanye Stillwater’s Kroondal operations. The dispute comes after wage negotiations deadlocked, the union said on Saturday. READ: Two miners killed at Impala Mine in Rustenburg Num is demanding R10,500 a month for some categories of workers and a 15 percent hike for another category. The company is meanwhile only offering a 5.5 percent hike and a R750 increase, NUM said in a statement. eNCA